The Client indemnifies the Consulting Engineer against all claims, demands, actions, suits, proceedings, loss, costs, damages, injuries or expenses suffered or incurred by the Consulting Engineer (including, without limitation, legal costs and disbursements on a full indemnity basis) as a result of:

(a)	the Client relying upon uncompleted drawings and/or documents;

(b)	any modifications to the drawings and/or documents made without the approval of the Consulting Engineer;

(c)	any third party relying upon the drawings and/or documents otherwise than in connection with the project for which the services are provided.

Either the Client or the Consulting Engineer may terminate this agreement upon the expiration of reasonable notice given in writing.  The Consulting Engineer may terminate this agreement immediately if any amount is not paid by the due date. The Client may terminate, and the Consulting Engineer may suspend its obligations or terminate, this agreement immediately if the other party:

(a)	is wound up or made bankrupt;

(b)	has a receiver, manager, receiver and manager, administrator, controller, liquidator or provisional liquidator appointed;

(c)	enters into any scheme or arrangement with its creditors;

(d)	commits a breach (other than payment of monies) which is able to be remedied but not done so within 14 days of a request to do so;

(e)	commits a breach that is not capable of remedy or is a breach of an essential term.
